# Security rules — Meavo org standard

Org standard (see STANDARDS.md §4 in meavo-agent-templates). Deviations for this repo are listed at the bottom.

## Auth at every layer

- Verify auth independently in: middleware (pages), section layouts, Server Actions, and API routes.
- Middleware passes `/api/*` through — never assume an API route is protected.
- This repo's auth gates: `auth()` from `src/lib/auth.ts` (session), layout guards in `src/app/(app)/admin/layout.tsx` and `src/app/(app)/hr/layout.tsx`, `requireUser()` / `requireAdmin()` / `requireHr()` in `src/lib/action-auth.ts`, and `isAdmin()` / `hasHrAccess()` / `canGrantHrAccess()` in `src/lib/permissions.ts`.
- Tool card gating: gateway is the **issuer**, not a consumer — gateway login is not gated by `ToolCardAccess`. Gateway manages grants for satellite apps; stable card IDs live in `src/lib/tool-card-registry.ts` (`defaultCardId`, e.g. `seed-sales-tool`). Never look up a card by `linkedAppKey` at runtime.

## Sessions & credentials

- NextAuth v5 JWT sessions; refresh `systemRole` / `hrAccess` from DB in the JWT callback.
- Passwords: bcryptjs 12 rounds, min 8 chars. Login throttling via shared `LoginThrottle` table.
- Google OAuth is invite-only — user must already exist in the DB.

## Routes & rendering

- Cron routes: `CRON_SECRET` Bearer auth on every `/api/cron/*` handler.
- `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` on authenticated layouts and DB-touching pages.
- Never return stack traces to clients in production.

## Headers & content

- `next.config.ts` must set: `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, `X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN`, `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`, `Strict-Transport-Security`.
- Uploads: Vercel Blob, 10 MB limit, validate MIME + extension, stream downloads via authenticated route, sanitize filenames.
- Embedded HTML: sandboxed same-origin iframe with CSP `sandbox allow-scripts`.

## Secrets

- No secrets in client code, comments, or committed files.
- Document env var names in `.env.example` only — never values.

## Repo-specific deviations

- Gateway login is **not** gated by `ToolCardAccess` (the tool-card rule above applies to satellite apps; gateway is the grantor). Admins see all tool cards on the home page without individual grants.
- `ADMIN_EMAILS` env var auto-promotes matching users to `SystemRole.ADMIN` on login.
- `HR_ACCESS_GRANTOR_EMAIL` env var restricts who can grant/revoke HR access.
- Library upload is additionally gated by marketing team membership (`MARKETING_TEAM_ID`) — see `canUploadLibraryAsset()` in `src/lib/permissions.ts`.
